data.name: Label39.ToolTip
data.value:
o Follow up can be for other things, not only ETAs. If the agent tells the customer that they will follow up with them till completion of order, the follow up date section must be updated to match whatever was promised to customer.
o If issue is not resolved (ETA not provided, answer not provided to client, etc.) the SR must remain open and we must follow up with the client until issue has been resolved.

data.name: Label29.ToolTip
data.value:
o No further action is needed to resolve the customer’s issue.
o If issue is not resolved (ETA not provided, answer not provided to client, etc.) the SR must remain open and we must follow up with the client until issue has been resolved.

data.name: Label28.ToolTip
data.value:
o SR Information
o Account Information
o Summary
o Detailed Description
o Client ID
o Country name if Global
o Order ID/Specimen ID –More Info Tab (if there are multiple CID / Specimen IDs, separate each with a comma in this field)
o Background Check Country and Platform - More Info Tab
o Authenticated Caller Tab
o Notes Tab (when applicable)
o Ensure correct return address and signature template is used if an email is sent to the client

data.name: Label25.ToolTip
data.value:
o There should be a summary line for every Service Request. The summary must be a brief and accurate synopsis of the reason for the call.
The Service Request must reflect the steps taken for resolution and should accurately reflect the issue that the client is experiencing.
o Notes in the Detailed Description are not required unless unusual actions were taken (escalation to Level 2, etc.).
If unusual action is taken, this must be documented in the Detailed Description tab.

data.name: Label26.ToolTip
data.value:
o When selecting a contact in the system (if there are multiple ones), select the contact that has the most correct information (account number, email address, telephone number).
You may then add any information that is missing (that you have obtained) to this contact.
This will eliminate creating duplicate contacts in the system. Please review with your supervisor the different ways to search for contacts in Siebel.
*
o If the contact is the applicant
* The proper applicant generic contact must be used
* The applicant name, phone number and email address must be included in the main Service Request section
* The Applicant Call box in the More Info tab must be checked
* Note: Service Requests must never be closed under First Name-change me Last Name-change me

data.name: Label27.ToolTip
data.value:
o The category/subcategory should reflect the issue of the chat. Reports are queried using this information. Using the correct options in this section increases the accuracy of our reporting.
o The General Questions option should be used only if there is not a category/subcategory that fits the issue or if it is truly a General Question.
o There is a list of Categories/Subcategories available.
See the Siebel Category Definitions job aid. Please review with your supervisor if you have any questions.

data.name: Label5.ToolTip
data.value:
o Chat requires the contact to be logged into a secure FADV portal, questions are only necessary if the Contact Data Page in Finesse Seibel does not have full information.
It is the agent's responsibility to make sure even though the user has the ability to access the portal and initiate chat, that they also have the appropriate rights in EA Admin/CustX

data.name: Label1.ToolTip
data.value:
o At the beginning of each chat the agent should acknowledge the client and offer assistance.
* The Quick Response is required:
* "Hello. Thank you for contacting First Advantage Customer Support. How may I assist you?"
*
o
* If the client provides the reason for the call before you can greet them, a branded greeting is still required.
* "Hello! Thank you for contacting First Advantage. One moment while I check on that for you."

data.name: Label22.ToolTip
data.value:
Did agent call/email client with detailed follow up or resolution within the timeline promised?
*
o Agent should complete follow up then reach out to client with result of research within the timeline promised to customer.
* Example- Expired ETA
* Agent emails CRRG with county, state, sub-order and applicant’s name
* CRRG updates WinESP with updated ETA or close case.
* Agent monitors WinESP for updates
* After system is updated agent contacts client with results

data.name: Label23.ToolTip
data.value:
Did the agent give a detailed resolution to client?
Did agent provide summary of next steps to be followed?
* A summary of follow-up items must be reviewed if follow-up is expected:If no follow-up is required agent must still quickly summarize all items they've assisted with to ensure that there are no remaining items outstanding.
o
* Summarize the specific candidate(s).
* What specific information is being requested (eta)?
* When can the client expect to receive a follow-up?
* If no follow-up is required agent must still quickly summarize all items they've assisted with to ensure that there are no remaining items outstanding.
* If issue is not resolved (ETA not provided, answer not provided to client, etc.) the SR must remain open and we must follow up with the client until issue has been resolved.
* In the event the chat is disconnected before the issue is resolved, Agent must attempt to contact the caller via phone or email to continue the conversation, provide the answer, or resolve the issue

data.name: Label24.ToolTip
data.value:
o The agent is expected to ask the client, when applicable, if there are any other issues that they can assist with.
This is not applicable “That’s all I needed.” Why: Helps reduce callbacks and identifies unresolved issues.

data.name: Label20.ToolTip
data.value:
Did we answer all the questions asked?
Did we research the concerns and find correct solution?
Were we thorough in our response to the client/applicant?
*
o The agent should ask questions and paraphrase to be sure that the issue is understood. By confirming the answers that the caller provided it also shows engaged, active listening.
The questions will also assist the agent in resolving the correct issue. If necessary, we must also offer to contact the client via phone if it is a complex issue, there are misunderstandings, or clarification is needed.

data.name: Label2.ToolTip
data.value:
o At the end of each chat, the agent should thank the customer for calling and Brand the company.
This shows our appreciation for the customer’s business and leaves them with the company brand firmly in their mind.
o The following must be included in the closing:
*
o “Thank you for contacting First Advantage.”
*
o Acceptable Alternates:
* “Thank you for choosing First Advantage."
o Unacceptable:
* “Thank you for calling"
* “Thank you“
* “Thanks! Have a great day”
* “Have a good one!

data.name: Label10.ToolTip
data.value:
o The agent should be able to locate and determine the information that can be provided by utilizing:
* F5, F7, F8, consideration codes, status codes.
* Drug Test, Clinic Information, Client Information and Scheduling Data using the CPScreen.net tool.
* Note that we cannot provide the following:
* Any information on internal searches that are being conducted for an NCRF.
* Specific court information
* The name of the person verifying employment/education
* Agent can confirm information but cannot provide information in regards to DOB, SSN, contact numbers provided, etc.
* Agent must avoid using the terms "we will escalate" or "I will expedite". This verbiage gives a false impression of how the process is handled.
* Instead, we can use terms like "I will follow up to have the order completed as soon as possible"
* Applicants may call in to provided Missing Information, however any other information will need to be obtained through Consumer Disclosure or the applicant may be referred to their recruiter.
The only general information that can be given to an Applicant is the “In Process” or “Complete”.

data.name: Label11.ToolTip
data.value:
o This section allows the Quality Assurance team to determine if additional training is required when navigating through applications and internal systems.
Effective utilization and navigation improves our accessibility and makes the chat more efficient for the customer.

data.name: Label12.ToolTip
data.value:
o Agent should follow all Client Fact Sheet instructions and internal tools (EA Admin / CustX) to ensure that the information being provided falls within the guidelines of the customer, account guidelines and the user rights of the customer.
The agent will then know what type of information can be provided: overall score or details. Providing too much information to a caller that doesn’t have appropriate rights will result in a deduction.

data.name: Label13.ToolTip
data.value:
The ability to project understanding of urgency and seriousness of all customers concerns.
We want to show that their request and concerns are as important to us as they are to them.
Examples of empathy:
*
o I can certainly help you…
o I assure you I will try my best…
o I’m sorry for the inconvenience that you have faced. What I can do for you is…
o Positive words-definitely, surely, absolutely, certainly and fantastic

data.name: Label6.ToolTip
data.value:
o Agent should remain professional, respectful, sincere and energetic while chatting with customer.
o Put yourself in your customer’s shoes. The agent should ask themselves, if the positions were switched, would they want to speak with themselves?
Try to imagine what the customer is feeling and respond accordingly. Using “Please”, “Thank you”, “Sir” or “Ma’am” demonstrates courtesy.
Different situations require a different response from time to time such as sounding empathetic, sounding confident when delivering information, conveying a sense of urgency and being sincere when offering help.
o Examples: “Mr. Jones. I’ll be glad to assist.” (Typed with a confident and pleasant tone or “smile” in your words)

data.name: Label3.ToolTip
data.value:
Did the agent use language that is considered easily understood by the client?
See common phrases to be replaced (https://confluence.fadv.com/display/SSW/***Common+Phrases+to+be+Replaced)
The agent is expected to avoid using internal terminology, acronyms, jargon or slang that can be confusing to the caller.
It is also the expectation that proper English be used, eliminating the use of slang.
*
o
* Jargon Examples: Avoid use of “PAID, DNP, EPP, FEMP, PEMP, etc.” Examples of slang: “Dude. Yep Yep. Alrighty. Cool beans.”
o Avoid Regional Terms Listed Below Bifurcate
* You need to take a call on this
* I will do the necessary or do the needful
* The same
* Back End Team
* Hence
* Request you do something
* Special/Relevant/Necessary/Correct/Appropriate Department/Concern Team

data.name: Label4.ToolTip
data.value:
o The process of researching and solving the customers concerns while keeping them informed of your steps
o Example – “I’m looking for the order, let me reconfirm the ID is….”
o Advise the customer of what actions or steps are being taken
o Gain customer’s permission before holds
o Hold times are limited to 2 minutes; after this timeframe the agent provides an update/reason and shows appreciation for the customer’s patience.
o If cumulative hold time is to exceed 5 minutes we must be present the caller with the options of continuing to hold or receiving a call back..
o The agent should avoid gaps of silence on chat
o In the event the Client does not respond to us, Agent must give the Client a total of 5 minutes before disconnecting the chat.
* After 3 minutes of no response, we must warn the client we will disconnect. Agent can use the No Response Warning Quick Response option
* "It's been some time since we communicated, I want to make sure you haven't disconnected. I will need to end this chat in two minutes if a response is not received".
* If the Client does not respond within the additional 2 minutes, the chat can be disconnected. Agent can use the No Response Quick Response option.
* "I am terminating the chat due to inactivity. Feel free to open a new chat if you need anything at all. We are always happy to help".

data.name: Label7.ToolTip
data.value:
o context,comprehensivness and consistency of the document;
o vocabulary, usage and sentence structure of the text
o Always proofread your responses before sending to the client to ensure proper grammar, spelling and punctuation.
o Professionalism should always be forefront in the agent’s responses.
o If there are ANY spelling, grammar or punctuation errors, these points will be deducted.

data.name: Label9.ToolTip
data.value:
o Be attentive to chat, carefully read the client’s questions or concerns, then respond to the client
o The agent should not make assumptions about the issue that cause unnecessary response
o Proper attention to chat allows the customer to feel acknowledged, promotes cooperation and reduces misunderstandings.
o When customer has to repeat themselves, it shows we are not fully engaged.
